FreeSense Web Gateway 2.0 is a complete outbound web security gateway powered
by a pinned Squid 7 build. It supports explicit and transparent IPv4/IPv6
listeners, tunnel/selective/full TLS modes, native policy and feed compilation,
local/LDAP/RADIUS/Kerberos identity, caching, shaping, parent proxies, ICAP,
optional ClamAV scanning, PF safety controls, live status and diagnostics.

The package is disabled after installation and defaults to HTTPS tunnelling.
TLS inspection requires an explicit acknowledgement and an internal CA.
